            <head xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-Hd1e108">Rubrica 10</head>
            <head xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-Hd1e111" type="question-title">De coniectura morum per aspectum et gestus</head>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-d1e114">
              De coniectura morum per 
              aspectum et gestum. Rubrica. 10
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-d1e121">
              <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-Rd1e117">SAlomon in prouerb. ca.
              17.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-Qd1e127">In facie
              prudentis lucet prudentia.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-d1e133"> 
              <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-Rd1e130">17. c.</ref>
              <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-Qd1e135">Quodo in aquis resplendent vultus 
              prospicientium: sic corda hominum manifesta sunt
              prudentibus.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-d1e146"> 
              <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-Rd1e144">Idem in eccl. c. 8.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-Qd1e148">Sapientia
              hominis lucet in vultu eius.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-d1e154">
              <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-Rd1e156">Aristoteles ethicorum libro 4. c. 8.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-Qd1e158">Unusquisque
              qualis est talia dicit: et operatur: et sic viuit.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-d1e164">
              <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-Rd1e168">10. c. et fi.</ref>  <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-Qd1e168">Rubescunt verecundati: mortem autem
              <sic>trmentes</sic> pallescunt.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-d1e174"> /
              <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-Rd1e179">Li. 10. et fi. c. 5.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-Qd1e176">
              Unusquisque circa hec et in his operatur que maxime
              diligit.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-d1e184"> 
              <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-Rd1e191">Idem retho. lib. i. c. 16.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-Qd1e186">Opera signa
              habitus sunt.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-d1e192">
              <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-Rd1e203">Iesus filius sirach in eccl. c. 13.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-Qd1e196">Cor hominis
              inmutat faciem illius: siue in bono siue in 
              malo.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-d1e205"> /
               <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-Rd1e216">19. c.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-Qd1e207">Ex visu cognoscitur vir: et ab 
               occursu faciei congnoscitur sensatus. Amictus 
               corporis risus dentium: et ingressus hominis 
               enunciant de illo.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-d1e217"> /
               <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-Rd1e230">21 c.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-Qd1e219">Fatuus ridens exaltat 
               vocem suam: vir autem sapiens vix tacite ridet.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-d1e225">
              <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-Rd1e242">24 c.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-Qd1e229">Diuitis et pauperis cor bonum in omni 
              tempore vultus illorum hilaris. Fornicatio 
              mulieris in extollentia oculorum et in palpebris illius
              agnoscetur.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-d1e235">
              <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-Rd1e258">Terentius in heutontumerumenon. c. 20</ref>
              <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-Qd1e237">Uultus quoque hominum fingit scelus.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-d1e243">
              <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-Rd1e269">Tullius de oratore li. 2.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-Qd1e247">Imago animi est 
              vultus: iudices oculi: nam hoc est vna pars 
              corporis que quot animi motus sunt: tot 
              significationes possit efficere.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-d1e257">
              <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-Rd1e285">Ouidius de arte amandi li. 3. et fi.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-Qd1e261">Sepe 
              tacens odii semina vultus habet.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-d1e267"> 
              <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-Rd1e296">Idem de luco</ref>
              <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-Qd1e269">Et color et macies et vestis et omnis egestas.
              Ostendunt qualem sensum sub pectore gestas</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-d1e282">
              <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-Rd1e313">Mattheus in euangel. c. 6.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-Qd1e286">Lucerna 
              corporis tui est oculus tuus: si oculus tuus simplex
              fuerit: totum corpus tuum lucidum erit. Si autem 
              oculus tuus nequam fuerit totum corpus tuum 
              tenebrosum erit.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-d1e298"> 
              <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-Rd1e329">Idem dicit lucas in euang. 16. c.</ref>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-d1e304">
              <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-Rd1e336">Seneca tragediarum in tieste. c. 8.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-Qd1e308">Heret in
              vultum trucis: imago facti.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-d1e314">
              <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-Rd1e348">Maximianus:</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-Qd1e318">Certe difficile est 
              abscondere pectoris estus.
              Panditur in clauso sepius ore furor.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-d1e326">
              <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-Rd1e362">Prudentius de psicomachia. c. 10</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-Qd1e330">
              Pallor in ore: Conscius audacis: facti dat signa
              reatus.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-d1e338">
              <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-Rd1e377">Marcialis cocus li. vndique suscepto:</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-Qd1e342">Est
              speculum mentis facies: oculique reuelant
              Qualia sint intus: mens animusque hominis.</quote> <!--'u' in "Qualia" flipped-->
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-d1e351">
              <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-Rd1e393">Ambrosius de officiis li. 2. c. 12.</ref>
              <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-Qd1e355">Degeneres animos vita arguit.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-d1e361">
              <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-Rd1e404">Prosper. sub. 22. epigramate.</ref>
              <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-Qd1e365">Ex operum specie clarebunt intima cordis.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-d1e371">
              <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-Rd1e415">Cassiodorus epistolarum li. 3. epi 3</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-Qd1e375">
              Panditur animi natura per vultum.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-d1e381"> 
              <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-Rd1e425">Li. 6. e. 9.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-Qd1e383">
              Superbus varieatis gressibus patet. Iracundus 
              luminum feruore declaratur. Subdolus 
              terrenum semper amat aspectum. Leues inconstantia
              prodit oculorum. Auarus ab vncis: vnguibus
              explanatur.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-d1e397"> 
              <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-Rd1e443">16. e.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-Qd1e399">Sollicitis inquisitoribus
              sepe et vultu proditur quod tacetur.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-d1e405"> 
              <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-Rd1e454">Li. 17. et fi.</ref>
              <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-Qd1e407">Sicut discipuli magistri scientiam produnt: sic nos
              obsequentium mores aperiunt.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-d1e416"> /
              <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-Rd1e465">Lib. 7. e. 5.</ref>
              <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-Qd1e418">Prima fronte talis dominus esse creditur: quale eius
              habitaculum comprobatur.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-d1e426">
              <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-Rd1e478">Isidorus soliloquiorum lib. 2. c. 29.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-Qd1e430">Animus
              in corporis habitu apparet.
              Gestus corporis signum est mentis.
              Corporis gestu: animus panditur.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-d1e440">
              <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-Rd1e494">Auctor libri qui dicitur pamphilus. c. 37.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-Qd1e444">Uix
              celari potest intimus cordis amor.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-d1e450">
              <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-Rd1e504">Cap. 43</ref>
              <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-Qd1e452">Occultare nequit sua lumina maximus ignis
              Occultare potest nec sua vota venus.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-d1e460">
              <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-Rd1e517">Andreas capellanus: ad gualterium de 
              amore li. i.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-Qd1e464">Exterior habitus manifeste 
              demonstrat qualis sit intus dispositio mentis.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-d1e472">
              <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-Rd1e533">Gualterius de castellione alexandreidos
              li. i.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-Qd1e476">O quam difficile est studium: non perdere vultu.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-d1e489">
              <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-Rd1e552">Mattheus vindocinensis in poetria: parte
              i. c. 12.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-Qd1e493">Oppositi vultus esse propheta potest</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-d1e499">
              <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-Rd1e565">Capitulo. 19.</ref>
              <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-Qd1e503">Est color interpres mentis: vultusque propheta
              Coniectura patet expositiua mali.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-d1e511">
              <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-Rd1e578">Particula. 2. c. 3.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-Qd1e515">Mens vultu loquitur
              habitusque propheta doloris.
              Coniecturales exhibet ore notas.
              Ira patet vultus exteriora nota.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-d1e525">
              <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-Rd1e594">Heinricus samariensis li. i. parte. i.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-Qd1e529">Iam 
              facies habitum mentis studiumque fatetur.
              Mensque quod intus agit: iudicat illa foris.
              Internique status liber est: et pagina vultus.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-d1e539">
              <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-Rd1e610">Gaufridus in poetria. c. 75.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d47635-Qd1e543">Formido 
              pallet: rubet ira: superbia turget.</quote>
            </p>
         </div>
